This paper deals with revenue maximization in auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.AI) techniques to determine the optimal prices for the items. The concept of revenue maximization is closely related to mechanism design (cs.EC), which is another sub-category that this paper could belong to. Finally, the use of Myerson's price, which is a well-known technique in auction theory, could also place this paper in the sub-category of learning in games (cs.LG).
